bric:\n  - Leaves (65200/65201) have 2 neighbors each (both spines) with State/PfxRcd = 1 per neighbor.\n  - Spines have 3 neighbors each (super-spine + both leaves); routes present to both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24.\n  - Super-spine has 2 neighbors (both spines) with PfxRcd = 2 from each.\n- Route tables:\n  - leaf_router_0_0: has BGP route to 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.4 (towards spine_router_0_0).\n  - leaf_router_0_1: has BGP route to 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6.\n  - Both spines have BGP routes to 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 via the correct leaf-facing interfaces.\n- Conclusion: Control plane is converged and advertising the expected /24 host networks; no BGP anomalies detected.\n\nAnomalies Detected\n- End-to-end host connectivity between pc_0_0 and pc_0_1 is broken due to failure on the 10.0.1.0/24 access segment:\n  - pc_0_1 NIC is down and has no routing table.\n  - leaf_router_0_1 cannot resolve ARP for 10.0.1.2 (incomplete ARP), causing ICMP Host Unreachable to be sent upstream.\n\nFault Localization\n- Faulty component: pc_0_1 (host) or its immediate L2 link to leaf_router_0_1 (leaf eth2 <-> host eth0). The rest of the fabric (leaves-spines-super spine) is healthy.\n- Fabric transport is functional, demonstrated by successful pings to the 10.0.1.1 SVI from multiple other nodes.\n\nRoot Cause\n- pc_0_1’s interface eth0 is administratively or operationally down. This results in:\n  - No L2 adjacency on 10.0.1.0/24.\n  - No ARP resolution for 10.0.1.2 on leaf_router_0_1.\n  - pc_0_1 lacking default route and unable to reach its gateway.\n  - Upstream ICMP “Destination Host Unreachable” responses when attempting to reach pc_0_1 from elsewhere.\n\nImpact Assessment\n- Traffic to/from host pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2) is disrupted.\n- All other fabric routing and intra-fabric reachability to leaf SVIs is normal. The issue is isolated to the access edge of subnet 10.0.1.0/24 at pc_0_1.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": 